Nguyễn Anh Tuấn is an Intern Tester with no commercial experience, but a strong foundation built through academic projects. Their core expertise lies in Manual Testing, Test Case Writing, Test Plan Writing, Software Testing Life Cycle (STLC), Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC), Bug Reporting, SRS Analysis, and Module Interaction Testing, with an understanding of Automation Testing principles. Their academic project, 'Restaurant Management Software Gimji', provided hands-on experience as a Tester in a 5-member team, where they analyzed SRS documents, developed test plans and methods, wrote and refined test cases, performed unit testing, checked module interactions, and meticulously reported and tracked bug resolution.
Technically, they are proficient in web fundamental languages HTML and CSS, alongside strong SQL skills for database interaction. Their practical experience includes applying these skills in the context of Manual Testing, Test Case Writing, and Bug Reporting within the Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) and Software Testing Life Cycle (STLC), demonstrating a solid grasp of software quality assurance processes. They possess an Intermediate English proficiency (B1 Preliminary) and are pursuing a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science.